027280439=3D""><p>Connections to the Common Core State Standards</p><p><str=
ong>High School: Geometry</strong></p><ul style=3D"list-style-type:disc;"><=
li><strong>Congruence</strong><ul style=3D"list-style-type:disc;"><li><stro=
ng>Experiment with transformations in the plane.</strong><ul style=3D"list-=
style-type:disc;"><li>G.CO.4. Develop definitions of rotations, reflections=
, and translations in terms of angles, circles, perpendicular lines, parall=
el lines, and line segments.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Understand=
 congruence in terms of rigid motions.</strong><ul style=3D"list-style-type=
:disc;"><li>G.CO.6. Use geometric descriptions of rigid motions to transfor=
m figures and to predict the effect of a given rigid motion on a given figu=
re; given two figures, use the definition of congruence in terms of rigid m=
otions to decide if they are congruent.</li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>Grade=
 8</strong></p><ul style=3D"list-style-type:disc;"><li><strong>Geometry</st=
rong><ul style=3D"list-style-type:disc;"><li><strong>Understand congruence =
and similarity using physical models, transparencies, or geometry software.=
</strong><ul style=3D"list-style-type:disc;"><li>8.G.1. Verify experimental=
ly the properties of rotations, reflections, and translations. <ul style=3D=
"list-style-type:disc;"><li>Lines are taken to lines, and line segments to =
line segments of the same length.</li><li>Angles are taken to angles of the=
 same measure.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div></div></div></a=
